'''Ismail Hasham''' (also known as ''[[Hajji|Haji]] Ismail Hasham'') was a late 19th century Indian businessman and the founder of [[Bombay Steam Navigation Company]], the first Indian owned shipping company.<ref name="ts_rashman_background">{{cite web |title=Training Ship Rahaman: Background |url=http://tsrahaman.org/background.htm |website=Training Ship Rahaman |accessdate=26 September 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927212837/http://tsrahaman.org/background.htm |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df= }}</ref>

