{{Spanish name|Boula|Senobua}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Kike | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Enirique Boula Senobua | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|1|17|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Malabo]], Equatorial Guinea | height = {{height|m=1.74}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]] | clubnumber = 19 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Oriente | youthyears2 = 2008–2012 | youthclubs2 = [[UD Almería|Almería]] | years1 = 2012–2013 | clubs1 = [[UD Almería B|Almería B]] | caps1 = 27 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2013–2015 | clubs2 = [[RCD Mallorca B|Mallorca B]] | caps2 = 41 | goals2 = 5 | years3 = 2015–2016 | clubs3 = [[Linares Deportivo|Linares]] | caps3 = 28 | goals3 = 2 | years4 = 2016–2017 | clubs4 = [[PGS Kissamikos F.C|Kissamikos]] | caps4 = 24 | goals4 = 2 | years5 = 2017– | clubs5 = [[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]] | caps5 = 19 | goals5 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2015– | nationalteam1 = [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] | nationalcaps1 = 17 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 12:06, 8 July 2018 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 11 October 2016 }}
'''Enrique Boula Senobua''' (born 17 January 1993), commonly known as '''Kike''', is an Equatoguinean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]] in [[Superleague Greece]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].
==Club career== Born in [[Malabo]], Kike graduated from [[UD Almería]]'s youth setup. He made his senior debuts with [[UD Almería B|the reserves]] in the [[2011–12 Segunda División B|2011–12 campaign]], in [[Segunda División B]].<ref name="sync">{{cite web|url=http://www.elalmeria.es/article/deportes/1419019/aleix/y/kikesincronizados.html|title=Aleix y Kike sincronizados|trans-title=Aleix and Kike synchronized|publisher=El Almería|language=es|date=14 December 2012|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>
In the 2013 summer Kike joined another [[reserve team]], [[RCD Mallorca B]] in [[Tercera División]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariorombe.es/fichajes-de-nuevos-jugadores-guineoecuatorianos/|title=Fichajes de nuevos jugadores Guineoecuatorianos|trans-title=Signing of new Equatoguinean players|publisher=Diario Rombe|language=es|date=23 August 2013|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref> On 11 July 2015 he signed for [[Linares Deportivo]], [[2014–15 Tercera División|newly promoted to the third level]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ideal.es/jaen/deportes/futbol-provincial/201507/10/linares-ficha-kike-boula-20150710142725.html|title=El Linares ficha a Kike Boula y renueva por dos años a Lopito|trans-title=Linares signs Kike Boula and renews for two years with Lopito|publisher=Ideal|language=es|date=11 July 2015|accessdate=2 August 2015}}</ref> On sumeer 2016, he signed with Greek [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]] club [[PGS Kissamikos F.C|Kissamikos]]. On 23 June 2017, [[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]] officially announced the capture of Equatoguinean international winger Enrique "Kike" Boula Senobua, who was released from Kissamikos.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thrakitoday.com/2017/06/enrique-boula-senobua.html|title=Δεύτερη μεταγραφή για την Ξάνθη. Ανακοίνωσε τον Enrique Boula Senobua |publisher=www.thrakitoday.com |language=ens|date=24 June 2016}}</ref>
==International career== On 3 January 2015 Kike was included in [[Esteban Becker]]'s [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] 23-men list for the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolbalear.es/2015/01/03/kike-boula-convocado-por-guinea-ecuatorial/|title=Kike Boula convocado por Guinea Ecuatorial|trans-title=Kike Boula called up for Equatorial Guinea|publisher=Fútbol Balear|language=es|date=3 January 2015|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref> Four days later he made his full international debut, coming on as a second half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 1–1 [[Exhibition match|friendly]] draw against [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guineaecuatorialpress.com/noticia.php?id=6095|title=Hopeful tie of the Nzalang against Cape Verde|publisher=Equatorial Guinea|date=8 January 2015|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>
==Personal life== Kike's cousin [[José Luis Senobua García|Sena]], was also a footballer. A [[midfielder]], he too was groomed at Almería's youth system.<ref name="sync"/>
